  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance to Displaced Populations in the Lake Chad Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lake Chad is surrounded by various conflict-affected areas leading to ongoing displacement and mobility, including refugee or returnee movements which have been ongoing in the region for decades. Through this project IOM is supporting a response within three of the most affected countries covering shelter and non-food item provision for most vulnerable displaced people; mobility mapping to ensure timely and precise information on the needs of displaced populations to support more accurate and effective decision-making processes of the humanitarian community and governments and lastly mental health &amp; psychosocial support (MHPSS). The MHPSS includes a participatory approach for victims or survivors of violence by providing victim-/survivor-centred and community and culturally sensitive services contributing to reducing psychosocial vulnerabilities and promoting community resilience and ownership.</narrative>
  </description>
